# Terminology

Use the following terms consistently.
Do not use listed variants unless they appear in code, URLs, or direct quotations.

| Required term         | Do not use                                    |
|-----------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| Web3Signer            | web3signer, Web3signer, web3Signer           |
| JSON-RPC              | json-rpc, Json-RPC, JSONRPC                   |
| REST API              | rest api, Rest API                            |
| key manager API       | keymanager API                                |
| slashing protection   | slash protection                              |
| Ethereum mainnet      | Mainnet (without "Ethereum" on first mention) |
| validator key         | validator private key (unless distinction needed) |
| TLS                   | tls (except in code/config snippets)          |

## Standards and specifications

On first mention in a page, spell out standards with identifier in parentheses.
Use the short form after first use.

Examples:

- First use: "Ethereum Improvement Proposal 2335 (EIP-2335)"
- Subsequent: "EIP-2335"
